<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> has been designed to be relatively easy to install on standard "vanilla" hardware and software platforms.  To set up your own <%= application.name %> instance, you will need the following items:</p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-cog"></i>Hardware Requirements</h2>
			<p>We recommend that you use a server with the following minimum requirements: </p>
			<div class="well">
				<ul>
					<li>2GB RAM</li>
					<li>20GB Storage</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-laptop"></i>Platform Requirements</h2>
			<p>You will need the following.</p>
			<div class="well">
				<ul>
					<li>PHP >= 8.1</li>
					<li>Must be able to run the PHP Framework, <a href="https://laravel.com/docs/7.x#server-requirements" target="_blank">Laravel 10</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<p> We recommend using a standard "LAMP" stack that integrates support for Apache, SQL, and PHP. </p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-database"></i>Database Requirements</h2>
			<p><%= application.name %> uses a standard SQL database. </p>

			<div class="well">
				<ul>
					<li>MySQL or</li>
					<li>MariaDB</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>